**Ideate:** Generate a wide range of ideas and possible solutions to the problem or opportunity.



I. Introduction

-   Overview of the design thinking process
-   Importance of the "ideate" step in design thinking

II. Understanding the design challenge

-   Review of the problem statement, user needs, and design challenge
-   How to keep the design challenge in mind while generating ideas

III. Techniques for generating ideas

-   Overview of various techniques for generating a wide range of ideas (e.g. brainstorming, mind mapping, lateral thinking, SCAMPER, etc.)
-   How to use these techniques effectively and overcome common roadblocks

IV. Encouraging creativity and divergent thinking

-   Tips and tricks for fostering a creative and inclusive environment
-   How to overcome creative blocks and biases

V. Evaluating and refining ideas

-   How to evaluate ideas based on the design challenge, user needs, and success criteria
-   How to refine and develop promising ideas

VI. Conclusion

-   Recap of key points
-   Discussion of the ongoing importance of generating ideas in the design thinking process
-   Encourage audience to practice the skills and methods presented in the lecture in their own design work.